FT  29 APR 93 / Observer: Outward bound
Creditors who don't want their money are a rare delight to administrators of
bust businesses. But there's a sad touch to one such jewel that has turned
up at Ron Robinson's Manchester insolvency practice, Buchler, Phillips &amp;
Traynor.
The self-denying creditor's reason for sacrificing the Pounds 30 debt reads:
'. . . as I am now aged 88 I may not be around when any repayment is made]'
To add irony to poignancy, the outdoor-equipment group that owed it - which
foundered last month - is named Survival.
